<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Problem: When pointing in config application.ini to load some plugins, such as:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
resources.frontController.plugins = Some_Plugin
resources.frontController.plugins = Another_Plugin
</code></pre>

<p>then Zend_Application_Resource_Frontcontroller trying to create them, but not to load. So, in projects, where autoloading is off, there isn't other way than directly include all plugin files in index.php</p>

<p>i think, it's bad practice. Especially, when i'm using different sets of plugins in different environments.</p>

<p>this is a very simple issue and only 3 lines of code fixes them. attaching them as a patch (to version 1.10.2)</p>

    </div>
